foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: During fiscal year 2019, as part of DOL’s continuing review of data in the SIMS-FOIA system, DOL worked to evaluate all aspects of the data in the system to promote more accurate data for tracking and reporting purposes. As part of this evaluation, we continued to review the data to identify requests that were received during FY2018 but that were not placed into active processing and tracking status until after the end of the fiscal year. During FY2019, we also identified instances where the system contained data inaccuracies such as requests that had been fully processed during FY2018 but that were not closed correctly in the system. As a result of these reviews, DOL found 489 requests that were not properly accounted for in the tracking system. These changes impacted the number of requests reported as pending at the end of FY2018. This means that the 1,500 FOIA requests that the FY2018 DOL Annual FOIA report reported as pending at the end of the fiscal year must be increased to 1,989 requests pending at the start of FY2019 as indicated in this annual report.

After reviewing its database, DOL adjusted the number of requests pending as of the start of the Fiscal Year for the following components: ADJ BDS, ALJ, EBSA, ETA, ILAB, MSHA, OASAM, OCIA, OFCCP, OIG, OLMS, OPA, OSEC, OSHA, OWCP, SOL, VETS, WB, WHD.

foia:OldestPendingRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: Some work day ranges reported appear to be out of sequence based on the date of the receipt of the request. However, this is attributed to requests that have been “tolled” once for clarification and/or “ tolled” on one occasion or more to resolve fee matters consistent with the provisions of the statute. Further, as the DOJ template will not authenticate data that is not in chronological order, some tolled requests have been re-aged to ensure that the reported data is in compliance with the established data protocol.
Due to system limitations, the charts in this section may contain information about unperfected requests.
